contest.winter2017

Class Tester

  • java.lang.Object
    • contest.winter2017.Tester

  • public class Tester
extends java.lang.Object
    Class that will handle execution of basic tests and exploratory security test on a black-box executable jar. Example code that we used to guide our use of Jacoco code coverage was found @ http://www.eclemma.org/jacoco/trunk/doc/api.html
    Author:
    IDT

        public boolean init(java.lang.String initJarToTestPath,
                    java.lang.String initJacocoOutputDirPath,
                    java.lang.String initJacocoAgentJarPath)
        Method that will initialize the Framework by loading up the jar to test, and then extracting parameters, parameter bounds (if any), and basic tests from the jar.
        Parameters:
        initJarToTestPath - - String representing path of the jar to test
        initJacocoOutputDirPath - - String representing path of the directory jacoco will use for output
        initJacocoAgentJarPath - - String representing path of the jacoco agent jar
        Returns:
        boolean - false if initialization encounters an Exception, true if it does not

      • executeBasicTests

        public void executeBasicTests()
        This is the half of the framework that IDT has completed. We are able to pull basic tests directly from the executable jar. We are able to run the tests and assess the output as PASS/FAIL. You likely do not have to change this part of the framework. We are considering this complete and want your team to focus more on the SecurityTests.

      • executeSecurityTests

        public void executeSecurityTests()
        This is the half of the framework that IDT has not completed. We want you to implement your exploratory security vulnerability testing here. In an effort to demonstrate some of the features of the framework that you can already utilize, we have provided some example code in the method. The examples only demonstrate how to use existing functionality.

      • instrumentAndExecuteCode

        private contest.winter2017.Output instrumentAndExecuteCode(java.lang.Object[] parameters)
        This method will instrument and execute the jar under test with the supplied parameters. This method should be used for both basic tests and security tests. An assumption is made in this method that the word java is recognized on the command line because the user has already set the appropriate environment variable path.
        Parameters:
        parameters - - array of Objects that represents the parameter values to use for this execution of the jar under test
        Returns:
        Output representation of the standard out and standard error associated with the run

      • showCodeCoverageResultsExample

        @Deprecated
private void showCodeCoverageResultsExample()
        Deprecated. 
        This method is not meant to be part of the final framework. It was included to demonstrate three different ways to tap into the code coverage results/metrics using jacoco. This method is deprecated and will be removed from the final product after your team completes development. Please do not add additional dependencies to this method.
